This PR adds injectivity lemmas for `Fin.snoc` and `Fin.insertNth`, similar to those for `Fin.cons`. This is part of #19315 that is split off.

nodes.body: Woops, forgot to propagate the theorem name change `cons_eq_cons` => `cons_inj`. Should be building now.

```suggestion
theorem snoc_inj {x y : ∀ i : Fin n, α i.castSucc} {xₙ yₙ : α (last n)} :
```
Shall I change the `cons_eq_cons` theorem into `cons_inj` as well?

```suggestion
theorem eq_self_or_eq_succAbove (p i : Fin (n + 1)) : i = p ∨ ∃ j, i = p.succAbove j :=
```

```suggestion
theorem insertNth_inj {p : Fin (n + 1)} {x y : ∀ i, α (succAbove p i)} {xₚ yₚ : α p} :
```
